heaviest_rainfall.status: Today ranked 7th for the heaviest total rainfall during a storm, dropping a total of 23.86mm of rain over the storm duration of 31.0 hours with a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 09 November 2025, with precipitation totalling 47.89mm.  The rain fell at 24.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 27.6mm per hour during the storm today (ranking 2nd from our records) and resulted in 5.35mm of total rain in 1.9 hours.  The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: A storm today ranked 7th for the longest continuous rainfall according to our records, lasting a total of31.0 hours.  It came with 23.86mm of rainfall, at times, falling at 8.3mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 24.6mm per hour.
